We will start with CodeSpaces on the Web:

https://devblogs.microsoft.com/cppblog/using-github-codespaces-and-visual-studio-code-for-cplusplus-development/
Using GitHub Codespaces and Visual Studio Code for C++ Development

Visual Studio and github.dev
Assume that there is no local version of Visual Studio Code and the laptop
Simply go to the remote github repository, and press "."

Visual Studio Code (VSC) and Codespace
Assume that there IS a local version of Visual Studio Code and the laptop
Connect to Codespace from VSC. 
Install the C/C++ Extension 

Throughout the class, we'll use the default configuration: 
Linux machine on the cloud with 2 cores and 32 GB memory. 

